NOTICE — Third-party code vendored in this repository
======================================================

This project vendors (copies verbatim) small parts of the ESA-ADB codebase so the
pipeline runs without cloning the full ESA-ADB repository.

Source repository: https://github.com/kplabs-pl/ESA-ADB
License: MIT (Copyright (c) European Space Agency, KP Labs, Airbus Defence and Space)
Paper: "European Space Agency Benchmark for Anomaly Detection in Satellite Telemetry",
       arXiv:2406.17826

Vendored files (verbatim, unmodified):

  src/m1_detection/vendor/algorithm.py
      from TimeEval-algorithms/subsequence_if/algorithm.py
      (the `subsequence_if` Windowed Isolation Forest detector)

  src/m1_detection/vendor/prep_utils.py
      from notebooks/data-prep/utils.py
      (preprocessing helpers: AnnotationLabel, encode_telecommands, find_full_time_range)

  src/m1_detection/vendor/timeeval_min/datasets/
      from timeeval/datasets/
      (ESA's multivariate fork of TimeEval dataset management)

  src/m1_detection/vendor/timeeval_min/utils/datasets.py
      from timeeval/utils/datasets.py

  src/m1_detection/vendor/timeeval_min/data_types.py
      from timeeval/data_types.py

  src/metrics_esa/  (ESA_ADB_metrics.py, metric.py, utils.py)
      from timeeval/metrics/
      (the ESAScores event-wise metric and its minimal import closure)

  src/metrics_esa/affiliation_based_metrics_repo/
      from timeeval/metrics/affiliation_based_metrics_repo/
      (affiliation-based P/R; carries its own LICENSE file, kept in place)

ESA-ADB itself builds on TimeEval (https://github.com/HPI-Information-Systems/TimeEval).

